event: response.output_text.done
data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_085efec7cce646e10169e47851abb08193847e44b719e45a66","logprobs":[],"output_index":1,"sequence_number":193,"text":"Yes—switch to door 2.  \nReason: Your door 1 is correct with probability \\(1/3\\). Since Monty always opens a goat and there are two other doors, the combined probability that the prize is behind either door 2 or door 3 is \\(2/3\\). After Monty opens door 3 to show a goat, that entire \\(2/3\\) probability transfers to door 2."}

